# Reflection

## What I Learned

Numbers can make a claim appear authoritative, but they still require verification. Precision, context, definitions, and the date of the information all influence whether a numerical claim is truly accurate.

---

## What I'd Do Differently

For real-world numerical claims, I would verify the figures using recent and authoritative sources. I would also distinguish between exact values, estimates, averages, and rounded figures to avoid overstating certainty.

